<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td><nobr><a href='tutorials/mac1984'><img width=9 height=20 style='margin-right: 10px' border=0 alt='Go back' src='intr/2captions/goback.png'><img border=0 alt='Mac Guided Tour' hspace=0 src='intr/2captions/macguidedtour.png'></a></td><td valign=top height=20><img width=19 height=20 align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3toprise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x'><img border=0 alt='Main menu' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3captions/mainmenu.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=20 style='background: url(intr/3topleftfill.png) top repeat-x'><img width=20 height=20 hspace=0 src='intr/3topleft.png'></td><td valign=top><img align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3topleftrise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>

<p>
<table class=reg cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 border=0>

<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/mac1984/023.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
If you&rsquo;ve already done the mouse exercises, and clicked on Continue at the very 
end, your screen should be displaying some boxes with different titles. This is the 
Guided Tour screen. 
</p><p>
On the left of the Guided Tour screen there are several titles, one for each part of 
this Guided Tour. At the bottom right is one that says &ldquo;I&rsquo;m ready to stop.&rdquo; 
Clicking on &ldquo;I&rsquo;m ready to stop&rdquo; will eject the disk out of the disk 
drive. You&rsquo;ll do that at the end, or when you want to take a long break 
from your Macintosh.  
</p><p>
At the top right there&rsquo;s a box that says &ldquo;Mousing around.&rdquo; Clicking 
on &ldquo;Mousing around&rdquo; will take you through the mouse exercises as many times 
as you wish, until you know how to use the mouse. If you&rsquo;d like to go 
through &ldquo;Mousing around&rdquo; again, stop your tape recorder, and start it again 
when you&rsquo;re finished. 
</p><p>
You&rsquo;re ready to start the Guided Tour. Each of the titles you see on the left 
is a short session playing back a series of actions on your Macintosh. This tape will 
tell you how to use your Macintosh, and the Macintosh itself will show you what the 
tape is describing. During these sessions, the Macintosh won&rsquo;t respond to the mouse 
or the keyboard. The actions you see on your screen were carried out and saved on your 
Macintosh beforehand. While these recorded actions are played back, your Macintosh cannot 
detect any present actions from the mouse or the keyboard. If you want to practice 
the actions you see and hear about, just wait until the end of the session. At the end 
of each short session you can either stop your tape recorded to practice what you&rsquo;ve 
learned, or continue to the next session. You can also repeat the session if you like. 
</p><p>
To start the first session, without touching the mouse button, position the pointer to 
point inside the box that says &ldquo;Show me my electronic desk.&rdquo; Don&rsquo;t click 
the mouse button yet. In a moment you&rsquo;ll hear a series of three tones. By clicking 
the mouse button as soon as you hear the third tone, you&rsquo;ll synchronize the actions 
on your Macintosh to the words on your tape. 
</p><p>
If you make a mistake in synchronizing the two, don&rsquo;t panic. Don&rsquo;t try to 
stop the Macintosh, let it run through the session. It is short, and you&rsquo;ll soon be 
back to your Guided Tour screen. Rewind your tape back to the three tones for that 
particular session, and get set to synchronize again. 
</p><p>
Ready to start on the first session? Be sure the pointer is pointing inside the box 
that says &ldquo;Show me my electronic desk.&rdquo; Listen to the three tones now. 
Without moving the mouse, click the mouse button as soon as you hear the third tone. 
</p></td></tr>

</table></p>

